## TEI Body Plan

The `<text>` element will contain `<front>`, `<body>`, and `<back>` as appropriate.

### `<front>` (if article has an abstract or prefatory matter)
- `<div type="abstract">` with abstract text if present

### `<body>`
- Top-level `<div>` for the article body
- Named subsections encoded as `<div type="section">` with `<head>` if headings are present
- Each paragraph → `<p>`
- Inline emphasis (italics, bold) → `<hi rend="italic">` / `<hi rend="bold">`
- Quoted titles → `<title>`
- Footnote markers in text → `<ref target="#fnN"/>` or `<note place="foot" n="N">` inline, depending on structure

### `<back>` (if article has footnotes/endnotes or bibliography at end)
- `<div type="notes">` with `<note xml:id="fnN">` elements for each footnote
- `<div type="bibliography">` with `<listBibl>` and `<bibl>` entries if a references list is present

